frameDefinitions: An Agent removes a Theme from a Source so that the it is in the Agent's possession.
A Lessee gains the use of Goods owned by a Lessor by payment to the Lessor.
A Gatherer removes Crop ripe and ready to an accepted degree.
An Agent performs a Response action in consequence of a Trigger event.
These are words describing a basic commercial transaction involving a Buyer and a Seller exchanging Money and Goods, taking the perspective of the Buyer.
A Recipient starts off without the Theme in their possession, and then comes to possess it.
frameExamples: Milton <t>took</t> the can of beer out of the refrigerator.
We are <t>renting</t> our apartment from a kind man named Tom.
They <t>harvest</t> their pumpkins in the Autumn. INI
I <t>respond</t> to earthquakes by hiding under my desk.
